-- Brazil Stock Movers: Embraer, Gafisa, OGX, Petroleo Brasileiro
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2012-01-02T20:51:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-02/brazilian-stock-movers-embraer-ogx-petroleo-gas-petrobras.html
The following companies had  unusual (IBOV) 
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index rose 1.9 percent to 57,829.27.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) rose 0.3 percent to 11.80 reais. The
world’s fourth-largest plane builder and U.S.-based Sierra
Nevada Corp. were awarded a $355 million contract to provide 20
A-29 Super Tucano aircraft to the U.S. Air Force, Embraer said
in an e-mailed statement on Dec. 30.  Gafisa SA (GFSA3)  (GFSA3 BS) jumped 8.7 percent to 4.48 reais.
Traders bet borrowing costs will decline after a central bank
survey showed economists covering  Brazil  cut their 2012
inflation forecast for a fifth straight week.  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA (OGXP3)  (OGXP3 BS) added 1
percent to 13.75 reais. The  oil company  controlled by
billionaire  Eike Batista  said in a regulatory filing today it
expects to start long-duration tests at its Waimea field on Jan.
23 after its OSX-1 platform received an operating license from
environmental authorities.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS) climbed 1.1 percent to
21.73 reais. Petrobras, as the oil company is known, declared an
oil and gas deposit in Brazil’s Guara area commercially viable.
The area has an estimated 2.1 billion barrels of recoverable oil
equivalent, according to a statement to Brazil’s National
Petroleum Agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
